Birds spotted around Tamaki Makaurau Auckland

What was the most commonly seen bird?

There are many birds you can spot around Tamaki Makaurau Auckland but which one did I see most commonly while collecting this data?

A bar graph showing that the most commonly spotted bird was a Tui being seen in 9 instances.

Tūīs were the most common! A native species that you can read more about here on the DOC website.

What kind of range was there in the number of birds seen?

Birds are often seen in groups called flocks, but which bird had the largerst range in their flock size?

A column graph showing the varriation in flock sizes of birds spotted with the largest range belonging to sparrows with a minimum flock size of 1 and a maximum flock size of 17.

Rock Pigeons a non-native species introduced to Aotearoa New Zealand being seen in a wide range of flock sizes ranging from a flock of 4 birds all the way up to flock of 25 birds.

When did I log the data about the birds I saw?

While I saw birds all throughout the day I often logged them at specific times, when I sat down to have lunch and when I got home in the evening after uni and work.

A denstiy graph showing the distribution of hours that sighing data was logged at having 2 notable peaks one at 12:00 and 21:00.

How often did I missidentify birds native status?

A bar graph showing the prportion of birds that were correctly or in correctly label as native or non-native.

About 55% of the time.
